    "summary": "The attack was initiated from address 0x0C8da4f8B823bEe4D5dAb73367D45B5135B50faB, which executed the primary attack transaction on Ethereum mainnet. Based on the incident classification and DeFiHackLabs proof-of-concept (Bedrock_DeFi_exp.sol), this was a price manipulation attack. The attacker likely manipulated the price feeds or liquidity pools that Bedrock DeFi relied upon for asset valuation, enabling them to extract value from the protocol at artificially inflated or deflated prices. The presence of WBTC (0x2260FAC5E5542a773Aa44fBCfeDf7C193bc2C599) in the referenced addresses suggests Bitcoin-related assets were involved in the exploitation path. Multiple protocol contracts were targeted in the attack sequence.",
